sketch-1.bodyMarkdown:
Different child classes can fulfill the same promise differently:

```python
class EmailChannel(NotificationChannel):
    def message(self):
        return "Email message"

class SmsChannel(NotificationChannel):
    def message(self):
        return "SMS message"
```

Both children answer `message()`. That shared method name lets other code treat them as a group even though the details are different.
